Mood Contract DApp
A simple Decentralized Application (DApp) that interacts with a smart contract to set and retrieve mood information on the Ethereum blockchain.

Smart Contract Details
Contract Address: 0x8a64Ce762C6A518Eb63F621D4Fccba584D4014Db
Contract ABI:
json
[
    {
        "inputs": [
            {
                "internalType": "string",
                "name": "_mood",
                "type": "string"
            }
        ],
        "name": "setMood",
        "outputs": [],
        "stateMutability": "nonpayable",
        "type": "function"
    },
    {
        "inputs": [],
        "name": "getMood",
        "outputs": [
            {
                "internalType": "string",
                "name": "",
                "type": "string"
            }
        ],
        "stateMutability": "view",
        "type": "function"
    }
]
Usage
Clone the repository:

Copy code
git clone https://github.com/your-username/your-repo.git
Open the index.html file in your preferred web browser.

Ensure you have a compatible Ethereum wallet (like MetaMask) installed and configured.

The application will prompt you to connect your wallet. Once connected, it will initialize the contract and signer.

Use the provided input field to set your mood and click the "Set Mood" button.

To retrieve your mood, click the "Get Mood" button.

Dependencies
Ethers.js
